  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> (skins on) into chunky chips</p><p>Spread them onto a baking tray and drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Put them in the oven for 35 min or until they're crispy and coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut the<strong> red onion[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Slice 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>red onion</strong> finely and finely chop the remaining</p><p>Strip the <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from the stems and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a large drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, then turn down to a low heat for 20 min or until the onion is soft and caramelised</p><p>Place the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in the oven to warm through for 5 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> lamb mince</strong> and half of the<strong> chopped mint</strong> and half of the <strong>garlic</strong> in a bowl (you'll use the rest in the next step)</p><p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix together (clean hands works best) and form 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>patties</strong>, then refrigerate them until later</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>cucumber</strong> in half, lengthways and scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon, throw the watery seeds away and grate the <strong>cucumber</strong> into a bowl</p><p>Add the remaining <strong>chopped mint</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and season lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, mix together and set aside</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the hot <strong>ciabattas</strong> from the oven and heat a wide-based pan over a medium-high heat</p><p>Slice the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in half and add them to the hot pan, cut-side down</p><p>Toast the rolls for 4 min or until slightly charred</p><p>Set the toasted ciabatta aside (keep the pan for the next step!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/329.step-6-x200.jpg",
